The statue was sculpted in 1939 in bronze dedicated to Joseph Joffre,French general officer during the first world war,craftsman of the Allied victory at the Battle of the Marne and the stabilisation of the northern front at the beginning of the war.He was named Marshal of France in 1916.It is located on other side of the street from the Ecole Militaire.

A very beautiful statue located in front of the Eiffel Tower and opposite the military school. Marshal Joffre, the winner of the great war. A monument erected between the two wars.

The statue of Marshal Joseph Joffre is a sculpture erected in front of the Grand Palais √âph√©m√®re in Paris. It pays tribute to one of the great military leaders of the First World War.  Marshal Joseph Joffre played a crucial role in the defense of France during the war, notably during the Battle of the Marne in 1914. The statue pays homage to him by representing his imposing silhouette and highlighting his role as commander in chief.  The Grand Palais √âph√©m√®re, where the statue is located, is a temporary building constructed to host various cultural and artistic events during the renovation of the Grand Palais. It is an emblematic place of the Parisian art scene.  The statue of Marshal Joseph Joffre in front of the Grand Palais √âph√©m√®re recalls the importance of his role in the history of France and his commitment to the defense of the nation. It is a symbol of gratitude to the people who sacrificed their lives for the freedom and security of their country.
